@startuml SuperAdmin_UC01-30_Analytics_Dashboard
title UC-01-30: Analytics et Monitoring - SuperAdmin (Dashboard Global + Details Secretariat)

actor SuperAdmin as SA
participant Dashboard
participant Systeme
participant DB
participant Logs

SA -> Dashboard: 1. Accede a Analytics
activate Dashboard

Dashboard -> Systeme: 2. Verifie autorisation acces analytics
activate Systeme
Systeme -> DB: 3. Verifie role SuperAdmin et permissions
activate DB
DB --> Systeme: Autorisation OK
deactivate DB
Systeme --> Dashboard: Acces autorise
deactivate Systeme

Dashboard -> DB: 4. Recupere metriques globales (nb users, nb secretariats actifs, nb clients)
activate DB

alt Erreur BD
  DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR: BD indisponible
  deactivate DB
  Dashboard --> SA: ERREUR 500: Impossible charger analytics
  deactivate Dashboard
else BD disponible
  DB --> Dashboard: Retourne metriques globales
  deactivate DB

  Dashboard -> Systeme: 5. Calcule KPIs globaux (paies/mois, revenue, taux churn)
  activate Systeme

  alt Erreur calcul KPIs
    Systeme --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Impossible calculer KPIs
    deactivate Systeme
    Dashboard --> SA: ERREUR: Calcul KPIs echoue
    deactivate Dashboard
  else Calcul OK
    Systeme -> Systeme: 6. Agrege donnees du systeme et genere indicateurs

    Systeme --> Dashboard: KPIs calcules (paies/mois, revenue, churn)
    deactivate Systeme

    Dashboard -> DB: 7. Enregistre log audit: Acces dashboard analytics global (timestamp, IP)
    activate DB
    DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre
    deactivate DB

    Dashboard --> SA: 8. Affiche DASHBOARD GLOBAL avec:\n- Metriques: nb users, secretariats, clients\n- KPIs: paies/mois, revenue, churn\n- Tableau secretariats (liste)
    deactivate Dashboard

    SA -> Dashboard: 9. Recherche/Clique sur un secretariat
    activate Dashboard

    Dashboard -> Systeme: 10. Verifie autorisation d'acces aux donnees du secretariat
    activate Systeme

    Systeme -> DB: 11. Verifie role SuperAdmin et acces donnees secretariat
    activate DB

    alt Acces refuse (donnees protegees)
      DB --> Systeme: ERREUR 403: Acces refuse a ces donnees
      deactivate DB
      Systeme --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Acces non autorise
      deactivate Systeme
      Dashboard --> SA: ERREUR: Vous n'avez pas acces a ce secretariat
      deactivate Dashboard
    else Acces autorise
      DB --> Systeme: Acces autorise
      deactivate DB
      Systeme --> Dashboard: Acces OK
      deactivate Systeme

      Dashboard -> DB: 12. Recupere stats detaillees secretariat (clients, paies, revenue, conformite ONSS)
      activate DB

      alt Erreur BD
        DB --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Stats indisponibles
        deactivate DB
        Dashboard --> SA: ERREUR: Impossible charger donnees secretariat
        deactivate Dashboard
      else Stats disponibles
        DB --> Dashboard: Retourne stats detaillees (donnees protegees)
        deactivate DB

        Dashboard -> Systeme: 13. Calcule KPIs specifiques au secretariat
        activate Systeme

        Systeme -> Systeme: 14. Agrege donnees secretariat et genere indicateurs

        Systeme --> Dashboard: KPIs du secretariat (paies/mois, revenue, conformite)
        deactivate Systeme

        Dashboard -> DB: 15. Enregistre log audit: Acces dashboard details secretariat (timestamp, IP, secretariat_id)
        activate DB
        DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre
        deactivate DB

        Dashboard -> Logs: 16. Log event: Acces analytics secretariat (monitoring)
        activate Logs
        Logs --> Dashboard: Event loggue
        deactivate Logs

        Dashboard --> SA: 17. Affiche DASHBOARD DETAILS SECRETARIAT avec:\n- Nom, TVA, stats clients, paies\n- Conformite: ONSS, donnees actuelles\n- KPIs specifiques du secretariat\n- Alertes applicatives
        deactivate Dashboard

        SA -> Dashboard: 18. Clique Configurer Alertes Secretariat
        activate Dashboard

        Dashboard --> SA: 19. Affiche form alertes applicatives (ex: taux erreur API > X%, temps reponse > Y ms)
        deactivate Dashboard

        SA -> Dashboard: 20. Configure alerte et clique Sauvegarder
        activate Dashboard

        Dashboard -> Systeme: 21. Valide seuils alertes (ranges acceptables)
        activate Systeme

        alt Seuils invalides
          Systeme --> Dashboard: ERREUR: Seuils invalides
          deactivate Systeme
          Dashboard --> SA: ERREUR: Valeurs alertes non acceptables
          deactivate Dashboard
        else Seuils valides
          deactivate Systeme

          Dashboard -> DB: 22. Enregistre alerte pour ce secretariat
          activate DB

          DB -> DB: 23. INSERT alerte (secretariat_id, seuils, admin, timestamp)

          DB --> Dashboard: Alerte creee
          deactivate DB

          Dashboard -> DB: 24. Enregistre log audit: Creation alerte secretariat (admin, secretariat, timestamp)
          activate DB
          DB --> Dashboard: Audit log enregistre
          deactivate DB

          Dashboard -> Logs: 25. Log event: Alerte creee pour secretariat
          activate Logs
          Logs --> Dashboard: Event loggue
          deactivate Logs

          Dashboard --> SA: 26. SUCCES! Alerte configuree\nVous recevrez notification si seuil depasse
          deactivate Dashboard

          note over SA, Logs
            **ALERTE CREEE OK:**
            - Secretariat monitore
            - Alertes applicatives activees
            - DB: Audit logs (qui a acces a quoi)
            - Logs: Events (monitoring temps reel)
            - RGPD: Acces loggues et limites par role
          end note
        end
      end
    end
  end
end

@enduml
